-- Cotton, Sugar, Soybean Futures in China Drop by Limit on Inflation Concern
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-17T01:26:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/cotton-sugar-soybean-futures-in-china-drop-by-limit-on-inflation-concern.html
China agriculture futures including
soybeans, sugar and cotton tumbled by the daily limit on concern
the government will curb speculation and take additional
measures to limit inflation.  Soybeans and soybean oil for September delivery both
dropped 4 percent to 4,337 yuan a metric ton and 9,396 yuan,
respectively, on the Dalian Commodity Exchange.  Cotton for May delivery slumped 5 percent to 27,090 yuan a
ton and sugar for September shipment also fell 5 percent to
6,196 yuan on the Zhengzhou Commodity Exchange.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 rdobson4@bloomberg.net  